<!doctype html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8" /><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" /><title>09 - Exceptions</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.5;padding:24px;max-width:900px;margin:auto}header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center}nav a{margin:0 8px}.section{margin:20px 0}.quiz-btn{display:inline-block;padding:10px 14px;background:#0078d4;color:#fff;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none}</style></head><body><header><div><a href="../index.html">◀ Back to course</a></div><div><strong>Java • Topic 09</strong></div></header><h1 id="title">Exceptions</h1><p class="lead">Checked vs unchecked exceptions, try/catch/finally, and best practices.</p><div class="section" id="overview"><h2>Overview</h2><p>When to throw and when to catch exceptions.</p></div><div class="section" id="details"><h2>Details</h2><p>Use try-with-resources for managing closable resources.</p></div><div class="section" id="practice"><h2>Try it</h2><p>Create a method that throws an exception and handle it.</p></div><div class="section" id="navigation"><nav><a href="08-polymorphism">◀ Previous</a><a href="../index.html">Course index</a><a href="10-collections">Next ▶</a></nav></div><div class="section"><a class="quiz-btn" href="#" data-quiz="quiz.json">Take Quiz</a></div></body></html>
